The paper deals with the complexity of online problems, which are typically studied in the subfield of computer science known as "online algorithms" or "competitive analysis". The paper also introduces a new complexity class, AOC, which is related to classical complexity classes such as NP and PSPACE. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), which is the primary subfield for the study of algorithmic complexity. Other likely sub-categories include cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
